<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>in someone’s arms • in someone’s hands</xh5><p> <i>in someone’s arms—</i>held by a person (lovingly) in both arms: On the dance floor, Kezia was whirling slowly <u>in the arms of</u> the Baron.</p><p><i>in someone’s hands—</i>in smb.’s power; under smb.’s control: She’s going to change the history of the country and the fate of the people is now <u>in her hands</u>.</p> </entry>
